The ISMEE method follows the same measurement procedure as the traditional MEE method, utilizing a control file created by the authors and installed in the measuring device. However, an improved symmetric multi-electrode array has been developed based on the following principles: A and B serve as the current-injecting electrodes, M and N function as the potential-measuring electrodes, and MA represents the separation between the M and A electrodes. It is important to note that the principle of reciprocity in electrical sounding has been applied, requiring the current-injecting electrodes to be positioned internally.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
